Normal AI Model
Traditional AI Development Process

To build a normal AI model from scratch, you need to complete three major stages.

1. Data Collection (3 Months)

First, you collect a large amount of relevant data.

Examples:

Images for image classification
Customer reviews for sentiment analysis
Medical records for disease prediction
English-Hindi sentence pairs for translation

The more high-quality data you have, the better the model can learn.

2. Train the Model (3 Months)

After collecting the data, you train the AI model.

During training, the model:

Learns patterns from the data
Adjusts its parameters
Improves prediction accuracy

Training often requires:

Powerful GPUs
Significant computing resources
Many training iterations
3. Deploy the Model (3 Months)

Once the model performs well, it is deployed so users can access it.

Deployment may involve:

Hosting the model on a server or cloud
Building an API
Creating a web or mobile application
Monitoring and updating the model
Total Development Time
Data Collection → 3 Months
Training → 3 Months
Deployment → 3 Months

Total ≈ 9 Months

